==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kieselguhr
<hw>Kie"sel*guhr`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr.
<ets>kiesel</ets> flint + <ets>guhr</ets> an earthy deposit or sediment
in water.]</ety> <def>Siliceous earth; diatomaceous earth; specifically,
porous infusorial earth, used as an absorbent of nitroglycerin in the
manufacture of dynamite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kieserite</ent>⟦br⟧
